# Backup & Export Integrity

## Canonical backup module

All export/import goes through `backup.py` — never duplicate zip logic in UI files.

## Required backup contents (v1)

Every valid backup zip must include:

| Path | Required |
|------|----------|
| `manifest.json` | Yes — `backup_version`, `profiles`, `files` list |
| `config.json` | Yes — profile registry + active profile |
| `profiles/{id}/data.json` | Yes per profile — daily life entries |
| `profiles/{id}/fitness.db` | Yes when file exists — SQLite fitness progress |

## When changing storage

If you add a new persisted artifact (new DB, photos dir, etc.):

1. Update `PROFILE_ARTIFACTS` in `backup.py`
2. Update `tests/test_backup.py` roundtrip test
3. Update Settings dialog copy if user-visible

## Verification gate

Before finishing any change to `profiles.py`, `storage.py`, `progression/db.py`, or profile paths:

```bash
python -m pytest tests/test_backup.py tests/test_profiles.py -q
```

Roundtrip test must pass: export → delete local files → import → data + fitness progress restored.

## UI

Settings → **Export This Profile**, **Export All Profiles**, **Import Backup** in `tracker.py` `show_settings()`.
